127
00:17:39,271 --> 00:17:42,704
<i>Before the first dawn,
there was a battle in Heaven. </i>

128
00:17:44,505 --> 00:17:46,733
<i>The Enemy was cast out
and fell to Earth... </i>

129
00:17:47,404 --> 00:17:49,029
<i>an evil star... </i>

130
00:17:49,837 --> 00:17:52,167
<i>broken in body but not in pride... </i>

131
00:17:53,538 --> 00:17:55,662
<i>consumed by envy and hate... </i>

132
00:17:57,104 --> 00:18:00,695
<i>it conspired to remake
man in its own image. </i>

133
00:18:01,570 --> 00:18:03,866
<i>And thus the enemy
created a machine. </i>

134
00:18:06,104 --> 00:18:08,797
<i>A machine that stripped the
souls from the dead and dying... </i>

135
00:18:09,037 --> 00:18:12,969
and replaced them with
its own dark essence...

136
00:18:14,737 --> 00:18:17,703
Neachdainn, founder of our Order...

137
00:18:18,937 --> 00:18:21,300
assembled the ancient tribes of man.

138
00:18:22,237 --> 00:18:25,260
<i>Together, they defeated the enemy... </i>

139
00:18:25,936 --> 00:18:29,369
<i>and sealed his machine
beneath the Earth. </i>

140
00:18:35,270 --> 00:18:38,531
<i>The war has broken the Great Seal
and awoken the Machine. </i>

141
00:18:51,836 --> 00:18:56,202
<i>Released from their prison
the mutants dragged every body... </i>

142
00:18:56,237 --> 00:18:58,725
<i>to the pit where the
Great Seal once lay... </i>

143
00:18:59,935 --> 00:19:02,026
<i>and deep beneath the ground... </i>

144
00:19:02,436 --> 00:19:05,402
<i>the gears of the Machine
began to turn again. </i>

145
00:19:06,536 --> 00:19:08,468
<i>Changing the dead and the dying. </i>

146
00:19:09,402 --> 00:19:12,561
<i>Mutating them into
the enemies of Man. </i>

147
00:19:38,602 --> 00:19:42,090
<i>Even the power of the four
Corporations couldn't stop them. </i>

148
00:19:46,335 --> 00:19:49,066
<i>The Chronicles promised us
that one would rise... </i>

149
00:19:49,101 --> 00:19:52,658
<i>and follow the path of Neachdainn,
down into hell itself... </i>

150
00:19:53,235 --> 00:19:56,201
<i>and deliver Mankind from oblivion. </i>

151
00:19:56,534 --> 00:19:58,363
<i>I travelled to
see the Corporations... </i>

152
00:19:58,868 --> 00:20:01,629
<i>to plead with them
to fulfil the Prophecy... </i>

153
00:20:01,767 --> 00:20:04,426
<i>and defeat the enemy of Man. </i>

154
00:20:27,500 --> 00:20:29,966
How much time do we have?

155
00:20:30,800 --> 00:20:33,028
Days. Less, maybe.

156
00:20:34,167 --> 00:20:36,030
Begin the evacuation.

157
00:20:36,733 --> 00:20:38,063
Evacuation?

158
00:20:40,766 --> 00:20:45,130
Move the key personnel
to off world colonies...

159
00:20:45,633 --> 00:20:49,121
and then we can
reassess our situation.

160
00:20:49,433 --> 00:20:51,558
Am I to understand that
you would abandon the Earth?

161
00:20:53,266 --> 00:20:56,061
Yes, Brother. You understand well.

162
00:20:57,799 --> 00:20:59,425
We are finished here.

163
00:20:59,732 --> 00:21:01,755
And even with all your ships...

164
00:21:02,533 --> 00:21:05,192
how many millions do you
think you'll leave behind?

165
00:21:06,333 --> 00:21:09,662
And do you think that the Enemy
will stop at this world? They won't.

166
00:21:10,398 --> 00:21:11,591
They'll follow you.

167
00:21:13,465 --> 00:21:15,488
They will follow you
no matter where you run.

168
00:21:17,799 --> 00:21:19,424
There is still hope!

169
00:21:27,365 --> 00:21:29,331
- What hope?
- Fulfil the Chronicles!

170
00:21:30,131 --> 00:21:31,960
Give me 20 soldiers and a ship!

171
00:21:32,131 --> 00:21:35,961
And what can these twenty do
that our armies could not?

172
00:21:36,131 --> 00:21:38,397
They can go where an army cannot.

173
00:21:38,432 --> 00:21:41,727
They can go down into the earth.
They can destroy the Machine.

174
00:21:45,664 --> 00:21:49,062
I know what you must be thinking.
You men of science, of commerce.

175
00:21:49,831 --> 00:21:51,456
But I am a man of faith.

176
00:21:51,764 --> 00:21:52,991
And I am asking you...

177
00:21:56,764 --> 00:21:58,286
I am begging you...

178
00:21:59,764 --> 00:22:01,093
Have faith.

179
00:22:02,431 --> 00:22:04,260
Not in me. Not even in this.

180
00:22:05,431 --> 00:22:07,124
But faith in Man...

181
00:22:08,564 --> 00:22:12,462
Faith that the ones you would
leave behind deserve a chance.

182
00:22:24,264 --> 00:22:26,957
- Where are we going?
- Come on. Hold on to the ticket.

183
00:22:29,697 --> 00:22:30,458
Run!

184
00:22:31,964 --> 00:22:33,021
Hurry!

185
00:22:35,063 --> 00:22:36,154
Come on.

186
00:22:50,363 --> 00:22:52,386
Leave it! Run!

187
00:23:13,028 --> 00:23:14,221
That's ours.

188
00:23:15,195 --> 00:23:16,752
There it is. Come on.

189
00:23:23,828 --> 00:23:25,351
Good boy, come on.

190
00:23:25,661 --> 00:23:26,922
Evacuation passes?

191
00:23:28,229 --> 00:23:29,320
But I had two tickets.

192
00:23:30,295 --> 00:23:31,726
I have it here, wait.

193
00:23:32,461 --> 00:23:36,450
- Take the child and leave her.
- Put me down!

194
00:23:36,995 --> 00:23:39,358
- Mum!
- Get off me!

195
00:23:39,995 --> 00:23:41,221
No!

196
00:23:41,895 --> 00:23:43,258
- Mum!
- No!

197
00:23:44,695 --> 00:23:46,126
No!

198
00:23:47,161 --> 00:23:48,252
No!

199
00:23:54,595 --> 00:23:56,026
No!

200
00:24:04,495 --> 00:24:07,086
Who could imagine we should
see days like these?

201
00:24:07,760 --> 00:24:09,487
You should have gone, Brother.

202
00:24:10,394 --> 00:24:15,156
The barricades are crumbling...
they'll be here soon.

203
00:24:15,861 --> 00:24:16,959
When do you leave?

204
00:24:16,994 --> 00:24:20,721
The absence of gravity interferes
with my digestion, so...

205
00:24:21,494 --> 00:24:24,426
I shall stay.

206
00:24:26,293 --> 00:24:29,555
Perhaps Man can make a fresh
start on the New Worlds.

207
00:24:30,460 --> 00:24:33,085
