00:51:06,150 --> 00:51:09,116
<i>HMS Tango-6, break off or
you will be fired upon. </i>

503
00:51:09,250 --> 00:51:11,442
Repeat, you will be fired upon.

504
00:51:14,050 --> 00:51:16,174
<i>You must break off now!</i>

505
00:51:20,850 --> 00:51:21,838
Fire!

506
00:51:22,817 --> 00:51:24,112
They're going to ram us...

507
00:51:24,249 --> 00:51:25,146
Fire!

508
00:51:39,383 --> 00:51:40,678
<i>Captain, I've lost them. </i>

509
00:52:00,515 --> 00:52:01,912
Get to the escape pod!

510
00:52:05,048 --> 00:52:06,946
Come on, let's get in the pod. Go!

511
00:52:07,081 --> 00:52:08,808
Let's go, let's go.

512
00:52:08,948 --> 00:52:10,175
Get in the pod.

513
00:52:13,482 --> 00:52:15,004
Go, quick!

514
00:52:15,282 --> 00:52:16,713
Let's go, let's go.

515
00:52:17,748 --> 00:52:18,839
The bomb!

516
00:52:19,748 --> 00:52:20,873
Where's the bomb?

517
00:52:21,115 --> 00:52:23,342
Come on, come on!

518
00:52:25,581 --> 00:52:26,945
Give me that damn thing. Come on!

519
00:52:29,848 --> 00:52:31,143
Let's get out of here!

520
00:52:36,048 --> 00:52:38,014
- Pull the fucking chute!
- It's not releasing.

521
00:52:39,948 --> 00:52:41,005
What are you doing?

522
00:52:41,182 --> 00:52:42,943
Manual release on the outside.

523
00:52:43,081 --> 00:52:44,104
You'll be killed.

524
00:52:54,514 --> 00:52:55,946
Here we go...

525
00:52:58,648 --> 00:52:59,841
Come on!

526
00:53:02,182 --> 00:53:04,773
Pull the fucking chute!
Do it! Pull it.

527
00:53:12,414 --> 00:53:13,880
What's going on?

528
00:53:14,381 --> 00:53:15,813
We're still falling.

529
00:53:15,947 --> 00:53:17,913
- We're too heavy.
- We lost the chute.

530
00:53:18,281 --> 00:53:19,577
Goddam it!

531
00:53:22,581 --> 00:53:23,569
Is there a back-up?

532
00:53:24,047 --> 00:53:25,637
Hit the back-up!

533
00:53:25,880 --> 00:53:28,369
- No!
- Fuck, no! Yes, motherfucker.

534
00:53:28,613 --> 00:53:30,476
Pop it now, we'll shred
it like the first!

535
00:53:30,747 --> 00:53:33,179
Open low, it'll slow us down
before we hit.

536
00:53:33,381 --> 00:53:36,108
- Before the silk rips apart.
- He's right.

537
00:53:36,281 --> 00:53:37,712
- What did he say?
- I've got not idea.

538
00:53:38,613 --> 00:53:40,340
- Juba's right.
- Hit the goddam backup.

539
00:53:40,513 --> 00:53:42,261
We've only got one chute left.

540
00:53:42,296 --> 00:53:44,011
We rip that one, we're dead.

541
00:53:44,280 --> 00:53:47,075
When we're lower, we'll pop it.

542
00:53:47,246 --> 00:53:49,712
- Hit the god dam chute.
- 1500.

543
00:53:50,113 --> 00:53:51,579
You better be right
about this, Juba.

544
00:53:52,346 --> 00:53:54,971
You sure you know what
you're talking about?

545
00:53:55,146 --> 00:53:58,044
You better be right about this,
you son of a bitch.

546
00:53:59,079 --> 00:54:01,568
244... 152...

547
00:54:01,879 --> 00:54:03,640
- Ready?
- Any time!

548
00:54:03,813 --> 00:54:04,779
Any time now.

549
00:54:09,380 --> 00:54:11,538
Open! Open now!

550
00:54:14,946 --> 00:54:16,844
- Now!
- Pull the goddam chute!

551
00:54:38,045 --> 00:54:39,170
There you go...

552
00:54:39,812 --> 00:54:41,573
Come on, give me that.

553
00:54:49,978 --> 00:54:51,239
The Captain's fucked.

554
00:54:59,211 --> 00:55:01,109
We'll cut you loose.

555
00:55:01,445 --> 00:55:03,638
It hit the artery.

556
00:55:05,077 --> 00:55:08,043
If you pull it out, I'm gone.

557
00:55:16,178 --> 00:55:18,041
- Amen.
- Amen.

558
00:55:31,811 --> 00:55:32,970
Sergeant Hunter.

559
00:55:35,343 --> 00:55:40,674
May I ask the borrow
of a grenade, please?

560
00:55:57,243 --> 00:55:58,334
Thank you.

561
00:56:01,943 --> 00:56:03,568
Good luck, Sergeant.

562
00:56:21,109 --> 00:56:21,708
White phosphorous?

563
00:56:21,743 --> 00:56:23,833
Conchita here, she's
a real spitfire.

564
00:56:24,242 --> 00:56:27,003
Just make sure you're not near
me when your gun blows up.

565
00:56:27,176 --> 00:56:30,767
- Where are we?
- Off by 4 leagues north-southwest.

566
00:56:30,975 --> 00:56:33,342
Gotta pass through the city
like the old monk said.

567
00:56:33,377 --> 00:56:34,399
Let's go.

568
00:57:11,074 --> 00:57:12,301
Check your targets.

569
00:57:15,341 --> 00:57:16,567
Two...

570
00:57:38,541 --> 00:57:40,006
Need a hand with that, boss?

571
00:57:41,740 --> 00:57:43,104
Be quiet.

572
00:58:09,406 --> 00:58:11,668
Refugees. Where the
hell are they going?

573
00:58:16,906 --> 00:58:18,202
Hunter?

574
00:58:36,039 --> 00:58:38,451
The current bid stands
at two gold watches...

575
00:58:38,486 --> 00:58:40,864
a diamond necklace, and
10,000 gold talents!

576
00:58:42,572 --> 00:58:45,333
Get out of here, go on.
Clear off, then.

577
00:58:45,905 --> 00:58:49,439
- Going once, going twice...
- I said, get back!

578
00:58:49,474 --> 00:58:52,064
Sold! To the skeleton
in the monkey suit.

579
00:58:57,771 --> 00:58:59,237
One ticket, not two!

580
00:58:59,704 --> 00:59:02,602
- I bought it!
- And she'll show her gratitude...

581
00:59:02,738 --> 00:59:05,602
cleaning my crap
from here to Mars.

582
00:59:05,971 --> 00:59:07,994
Unless you want to
buy another ticket?

583
00:59:08,905 --> 00:59:10,370
That's all my money!

584
00:59:10,704 --> 00:59:12,136
Then fuck off!

585
00:59:15,204 --> 00:59:16,898
Do you know who I am?

586
00:59:22,738 --> 00:59:24,203
That's who you are.

587
00:59:25,970 --> 00:59:29,266
Ass, stash or cash!
Nobody rides free!

588
00:59:30,004 --> 00:59:31,833
<i>I want everybody on in ten minutes. </i>

589
00:59:31,970 --> 00:59:33,095
We need to cut through there.

590
00:59:33,770 --> 00:59:34,793
<i>I want diamonds. </i>

591
00:59:34,970 --> 00:59:37,527
- Good place for an ambush.
- Can't be too many mutes.

592
00:59:38,070 --> 00:59:39,297
There's too much easy meat.

593
00:59:40,470 --> 00:59:42,148
All the more reason
for them to come.

594
00:59:42,183 --> 00:59:43,826
<i>I don't care whose... open it. </i>

595
00:59:44,271 --> 00:59:48,033
Come on, show us your money.
It's your life I'm talking about.

596
00:59:48,236 --> 00:59:50,532
Give me that... ah, fuck off.

597
00:59:51,004 --> 00:59:52,367
Let it go, Hunter.

598
00:59:55,870 --> 00:59:57,096
We go through the square.

599
00:59:57,737 --> 00:59:59,794
- We don't have time for this.
- Make time.

600
01:00:02,737 --> 01:00:05,100
The next one begins in 5.000 talents.

601
01:00:09,403 --> 01:00:13,096
Save yourselves.
Get your money out, come on!

602
01:00:13,536 --> 01:00:16,025
Any advance on 6,000?

603
01:00:16,236 --> 01:00:17,496
Come on, we haven't got all day.

604
01:00:18,236 --> 01:00:20,929
Price stands at 7,000 talents...

605
01:00:21,069 --> 01:00:23,126
three bottles of very
old Scottish whiskey...

606
01:00:23,836 --> 01:00:24,995
Get out of it.

607
01:00:29,036 --> 01:00:30,300
Let them on.

608
01:00:30,335 --> 01:00:31,596
Are you making a bid?

609
01:00:32,669 --> 01:00:35,066
First you take the kids
and then the women...

610
01:00:35,502 --> 01:00:37,468
and then you take the men
if there's any room left.

611
01:00:37,636 --> 01:00:40,965
Hey, Soldier-Boy. The ship
can only carry so much weight.

612
01:00:41,968 --> 01:00:44,059
Yeah? What do you weigh?

613
01:00:45,035 --> 01:00:47,297
- 275kg?
- 310kg.

614
01:00:56,368 --> 01:01:00,062
310, that's two women and
two kids. Come on. Let's go.

615
01:01:05,902 --> 01:01:07,868
- What do you weigh?
- Very little.

616
01:01:09,768 --> 01:01:11,358
Dump the luggage. Take them all.

617
01:01:26,667 --> 01:01:28,065
It's top.

618
01:01:28,334 --> 01:01:32,527
Church, it's not too far. It's just
in the middle of the old city.

619
01:01:34,434 --> 01:01:35,866
You figure out where
we're going yet?

620
01:01:36,201 --> 01:01:37,564
Straight on.

621
01:01:39,101 --> 01:01:41,498
Listen you endanger the mission
again, I shoot you myself.

622
01:01:41,901 --> 01:01:43,332
Why wait?

623
01:02:51,765 --> 01:02:53,061
Christ!

624
01:02:55,698 --> 01:02:57,493
What sort of church is this?

625
01:02:58,498 --> 01:03:00,054
How do you lose a city?

626
01:03:11,165 --> 01:03:13,358
The catacombs lead
down to the Lost City.

627
01:03:23,364 --> 01:03:24,887
There must be thousands.

628
01:03:25,397 --> 01:03:27,955
Each New Age builds upon
the bones of the old.

629
01:03:29,230 --> 01:03:31,219
How many times have
they come before?

630
01:03:32,731 --> 01:03:36,686
They didn't do this, we did this.

631
01:03:39,230 --> 01:03:41,423
We've always excelled
at killing one another.

632
01:03:43,431 --> 01:03:45,294
They would challenge our supremacy...

633
01:03:45,631 --> 01:03:47,823
as the architects of our own end.

634
01:03:48,797 --> 01:03:49,956
Halt!

635
01:04:06,897 --> 01:04:08,192
- Brother?
- Yes?

636
01:04:14,797 --> 01:04:16,387
The Lost City.

637
01:04:18,730 --> 01:04:22,287
That skyscraper, we need
to go down, deep into it.

638
01:04:24,396 --> 01:04:27,595
The City of the Ancients,
buried 500 years ago...

639
01:04:27,630 --> 01:04:28,959
in the Black Winter.

640
01:04:32,695 --> 01:04:35,321
- Holy shit!
- We're being watched.

641
01:05:22,861 --> 01:05:24,156
What are they?

642
01:05:25,828 --> 01:05:27,259
I have no idea.

643
01:05:38,860 --> 01:05:40,190
What's it say?

644
01:05:40,960 --> 01:05:42,653
"Abandon all hope."

645
01:05:43,693 --> 01:05:44,920
Motherfuckers.

646
01:05:47,627 --> 01:05:48,786
No shit.

647
01:05:59,627 --> 01:06:01,183
Jesus, that's deep.

648
01:06:01,627 --> 01:06:03,320
Someone's going to
have to stay up here.

649
01:06:03,627 --> 01:06:05,422
We don't want them coming
down on top of us.

650
01:06:06,827 --> 01:06:08,087
I got it.

651
01:06:08,993 --> 01:06:10,653
You watch your ass
out there, compaï¿½ero.

652
01:06:13,093 --> 01:06:14,582
It don't look that safe.

653
01:06:15,260 --> 01:06:17,055
Got to pay for those
tickets sooner or later.

654
01:06:18,993 --> 01:06:21,255
Take care of yourself, Juba.

655
01:06:23,426 --> 01:06:26,915
Sixty storeys. We'll go first
and let the others find the way.

656
01:06:28,559 --> 01:06:29,991
Yeah, what do you say?

657
01:06:34,492 --> 01:06:36,651
Brother, alright.

658
01:06:37,426 --> 01:06:40,551
This is the brake. It controls
how fast you go down, okay?

659
01:06:42,192 --> 01:06:45,352
You lift it up and
let yourself down.

660
01:06:46,292 --> 01:06:47,724
Punch it in, you stop.

661
01:06:51,526 --> 01:06:55,014
- That's it. Just take it easy.
- And this?

662
01:06:55,192 --> 01:06:57,249
That's the quick release.
Don't touch that.

663
01:07:01,192 --> 01:07:02,452
You alright?

664
01:07:04,125 --> 01:07:05,385
Let's go.

665
01:07:16,158 --> 01:07:17,283
20.

666
01:07:19,924 --> 01:07:21,550
How fucking deep is this thing?

667
01:07:30,791 --> 01:07:32,882
- It's getting hot down here.
- 40

668
01:07:43,323 --> 01:07:44,584
- Samuel?
- 55.

669
01:07:44,991 --> 01:07:46,014
How far?

670
01:07:47,524 --> 01:07:49,047
- Stop!
- 60

671
01:07:52,357 --> 01:07:54,653
- We're running out of rope here.
- We've gone too far.

672
01:07:56,457 --> 01:07:58,945
It's dark, God, it's dark.

673
01:07:59,657 --> 01:08:00,952
Something's not right.

674
01:08:08,890 --> 01:08:11,220
- It can't be.
- Got anything in that dammed book?

675
01:08:11,323 --> 01:08:12,720
What have I missed?

676
01:08:18,356 --> 01:08:19,788
We got people coming down.

677
01:08:23,723 --> 01:08:26,382
<i>Don't fall behind, Steiner.
It's a long way down. </i>

678
01:08:27,723 --> 01:08:29,382
<i>Yeah, all the way to hell. </i>

679
01:09:13,221 --> 01:09:15,016
Weird sounds down here, pal.

680
01:09:17,588 --> 01:09:20,577
It has to be here.
55, 60 floors down...

681
01:09:20,754 --> 01:09:22,982
there should be a ledge.
It says so right here.

682
01:09:26,021 --> 01:09:27,112
It has to be here.

683
01:09:40,888 --> 01:09:42,751
- Don't let me fall.
- I'm trying.

684
01:09:57,421 --> 01:09:59,353
You are a lucky son of a bitch.

685
01:09:59,653 --> 01:10:00,949
God provides, Sergeant.

686
01:10:09,553 --> 01:10:10,917
God provides.

687
01:10:23,453 --> 01:10:24,510
Close the gate.

688
01:10:25,886 --> 01:10:27,318
Hold up! Hold up!

689
01:10:27,653 --> 01:10:28,641
<i>Coming down. </i>

690
01:10:31,752 --> 01:10:32,945
We got an ugly.

691
01:10:37,652 --> 01:10:40,346
- We're bottled up in here.
- Wait! Use this.

692
01:10:42,719 --> 01:10:44,049
Grenade!

693
01:10:54,952 --> 01:10:56,474
- Grenade!
- Grenade!

694
01:10:58,752 --> 01:11:00,183
Don't drop that match!

695
01:12:02,383 --> 01:12:03,940
Go, go, go!

696
01:12:55,549 --> 01:12:57,776
- Any last words?
- Shut the fuck up!

697
01:13:21,015 --> 01:13:22,537
Are you well?

698
01:13:27,815 --> 01:13:28,837
Reload!

699
01:13:37,148 --> 01:13:38,011
Down!

700
01:13:53,747 --> 01:13:55,235
Anybody hurt?

701
01:14:06,380 --> 01:14:08,676
Hey... shit!

702
01:14:16,447 --> 01:14:18,571
Let's go... let's go.

703
01:14:29,147 --> 01:14:30,169
Dead end.

704
01:14:30,312 --> 01:14:32,972
- Anyone got a deck of cards?
- MacGuire.

705
01:14:33,980 --> 01:14:35,275
Figures.

706
01:14:42,746 --> 01:14:43,802
Thanks.

707
01:15:04,146 --> 01:15:07,270
They use tunnels to drag
bodies to the machine.

708
01:15:07,912 --> 01:15:09,901
It takes days, weeks even.

709
01:15:10,445 --> 01:15:12,104
You got a lot of faith in that book.

710
01:15:14,412 --> 01:15:15,934
You're wasting your time, Steiner.

711
01:15:16,111 --> 01:15:18,100
I will not let a handful
of rocks stop us.

712
01:15:18,412 --> 01:15:21,139
- It's a lot more than a handful.
- You find any inspiration?

713
01:15:21,512 --> 01:15:26,001
It's a very good book, but in the end,
even this book, is just a book.

714
01:15:27,878 --> 01:15:29,003
Well...

715
01:15:29,412 --> 01:15:31,707
And I take my Faith
from something Greater.

716
01:15:33,178 --> 01:15:35,371
Well, I haven't seen
much to have faith in.

717
01:15:35,611 --> 01:15:37,907
You have seen the worst
that Man can do.

718
01:15:39,978 --> 01:15:42,739
But you've not seen the
worst the Enemy can do.

719
01:15:45,111 --> 01:15:47,838
- So, who got your tickets?
- What?

720
01:15:49,144 --> 01:15:50,371
Your tickets?

721
01:15:50,544 --> 01:15:53,476
- What does it matter?
- It matters to me.

722
01:16:01,977 --> 01:16:03,409
Who cares?

723
01:16:04,577 --> 01:16:06,099
I'm sorry.

724
01:16:08,277 --> 01:16:10,799
Everything that is, comes from God.

725
01:16:12,110 --> 01:16:14,371
Everything is from God, and of God.

726
01:16:15,309 --> 01:16:18,275
The Enemy came from the outside.

727
01:16:19,877 --> 01:16:22,741
And as God is Life,
the Enemy is Unlife.

728
01:16:23,943 --> 01:16:27,602
It is the end of
every living thing...

729
01:16:27,910 --> 01:16:29,068
everywhere...

730
01:16:29,810 --> 01:16:31,275
and for all time.

731
01:16:33,109 --> 01:16:36,802
And so, I have Faith
that we will triumph.

732
01:16:39,610 --> 01:16:42,337
Because the alternative
is too terrible to contemplate.

733
01:16:43,143 --> 01:16:45,234
What if you don't believe in God?

734
01:16:45,410 --> 01:16:48,171
If you did not believe in God,
you would not be here.

735
01:16:51,342 --> 01:16:53,036
Are you guys gonna help?

736
01:16:53,375 --> 01:16:56,364
Maybe you haven't noticed,
but your mission is kind of fucked.

737
01:17:02,142 --> 01:17:03,870
You should have a little faith.

738
01:17:18,008 --> 01:17:19,338
Give me a hand.

739
01:17:28,775 --> 01:17:30,263
Something's down there.

740
01:17:45,608 --> 01:17:46,937
Hold up!

741
01:17:52,174 --> 01:17:55,368
Poor bastards! Looks like they've
been down there for weeks.

742
01:18:00,640 --> 01:18:02,197
We mustn't linger here.

743
01:18:05,440 --> 01:18:06,804
Where the hell are they taking them?

744
01:18:08,507 --> 01:18:10,666
Hunter? What is he doing?

745
01:18:12,907 --> 01:18:14,839
- Is that...?
- Sergeant?

746
01:18:15,140 --> 01:18:16,731
- Jesus.
- Top?

747
01:18:17,039 --> 01:18:18,062
That's Nathan.

748
01:18:20,173 --> 01:18:21,366
Fuck!

749
01:18:21,973 --> 01:18:23,200
Come on, let's go.

750
01:18:24,806 --> 01:18:26,067
It's just one man.

751
01:18:26,373 --> 01:18:27,702
I know that man.

752
01:18:30,806 --> 01:18:32,272
We have a mission.

753
01:18:46,572 --> 01:18:48,004
Vaya con Dios.

754
01:18:54,906 --> 01:18:56,064
Let's go!

755
01:19:54,637 --> 01:19:56,398
- Nate!
- Mitch?

756
01:19:58,104 --> 01:19:59,729
They got you as well.

757
01:20:00,370 --> 01:20:02,268
Don't talk. I'm getting
you out of here, pal.

758
01:20:05,537 --> 01:20:07,901
- Where are my girls?
- They're safe.

759
01:20:08,337 --> 01:20:09,701
They're halfway to Mars by now.

760
01:20:11,903 --> 01:20:13,130
Ready?

761
01:20:20,337 --> 01:20:22,269
We're almost there, keep going.

762
01:20:29,003 --> 01:20:30,299
What's that?

763
01:20:52,403 --> 01:20:54,198
What the fuck are you doing?

764
01:20:55,269 --> 01:20:56,928
I've got to find another
way out of here.

765
01:21:01,502 --> 01:21:05,265
I'm going to make you a sling...
get you out of this hole.

766
01:21:12,069 --> 01:21:14,899
- Mars, eh?
- Yeah... Mars.

767
01:21:16,035 --> 01:21:18,523
- How do you explain that one?
- I did a deal for a guy...

768
01:21:21,602 --> 01:21:24,568
Yeah, you know.
Save the world kind of thing.

769
01:21:27,868 --> 01:21:29,391
How's it going?

770
01:21:36,834 --> 01:21:38,130
Jesus!

771
01:21:40,467 --> 01:21:42,592
Listen to me. Listen.

772
01:21:44,601 --> 01:21:46,090
Finish your mission.

773
01:21:48,068 --> 01:21:50,727
I can't leave you here.

774
01:21:51,135 --> 01:21:52,430
I'm not asking you to.

775
01:22:06,833 --> 01:22:09,993
Tell Adelaide, and Gracie...

776
01:22:15,533 --> 01:22:17,726
Tell them, tell them...

777
01:22:19,000 --> 01:22:21,727
- Tell them.
- Right.

778
01:22:23,267 --> 01:22:25,199
- No.
- Right.

779
01:22:36,366 --> 01:22:37,593
You remember that...

780
01:23:09,165 --> 01:23:10,256
Help!

781
01:23:11,932 --> 01:23:13,693
The bag. We can't lose the bomb.

782
01:23:18,332 --> 01:23:19,820
Take it! Take it!

783
01:23:22,332 --> 01:23:23,695
Give me your hand!

784
01:23:39,364 --> 01:23:40,625
We must go on.

785
01:23:49,765 --> 01:23:52,788
- We have to go on!
- We're still human, Samuel.

786
01:24:02,564 --> 01:24:04,052
- Thank you.
- It's an honour.

787
01:24:15,697 --> 01:24:16,856
Fuck you!

788
01:24:52,262 --> 01:24:53,751
Oh, come on, give me a sign.

789
01:24:58,929 --> 01:25:00,121
Come on, fucker!

790
01:25:01,028 --> 01:25:01,959
No!

791
01:25:02,562 --> 01:25:03,993
No!

792
01:25:37,695 --> 01:25:39,024
Severian!

793
01:26:09,794 --> 01:26:10,953
El Jesus.

794
01:26:11,560 --> 01:26:12,389
Hunter!

795
01:26:18,627 --> 01:26:20,527
When's the last time you spoke?

796
01:26:20,562 --> 01:26:21,822
I can't remember.

797
01:26:24,560 --> 01:26:25,820
I couldn't save him.

798
01:26:27,460 --> 01:26:30,051
They dragged them
all the way to the Machine.

799
01:26:40,093 --> 01:26:42,558
- What are you doing?
- We need this damn book.

800
01:26:43,326 --> 01:26:44,314
It is not permitted.

801
01:26:48,092 --> 01:26:49,191
They took everything.

802
01:26:49,226 --> 01:26:52,215
He kept looking at this
damn stuff. What's it say?

803
01:26:53,393 --> 01:26:54,949
- I don't know.
- Read it!

804
01:26:55,925 --> 01:26:58,721
- I can't.
- Come here!

805
01:26:58,925 --> 01:27:00,653
Look, read.

806
01:27:02,559 --> 01:27:03,751
I can't read.

807
01:27:04,892 --> 01:27:06,188
You can't...

808
01:27:07,925 --> 01:27:10,289
How can you believe in a book
if you can't even read it?

809
01:27:10,458 --> 01:27:14,550
I don't need to read it
to believe that it's true.

810
01:27:19,225 --> 01:27:21,384
- That's the nature of Faith.
- Fantastic!

811
01:27:23,325 --> 01:27:24,951
What do you believe in?

812
01:27:29,525 --> 01:27:33,184
I'm not paid to believe.
I'm paid to fuck shit up.

813
01:27:34,692 --> 01:27:36,248
Are you coming?

814
01:28:08,990 --> 01:28:10,684
<i>Help me, please!</i>

815
01:28:14,957 --> 01:28:16,889
<i>Help me!</i>

816
01:28:17,524 --> 01:28:20,785
<i>Help me, please!</i>

817
01:29:03,256 --> 01:29:05,414
Shit! Duval and Steiner.

818
01:29:32,288 --> 01:29:33,844
Are you guys still alive?

819
01:30:00,354 --> 01:30:01,876
Can you still hold a gun?

820
01:30:02,154 --> 01:30:03,915
Only with my right.

821
01:30:07,521 --> 01:30:08,884
How about a rope?

822
01:30:16,520 --> 01:30:17,747
Just say when.

823
01:31:04,486 --> 01:31:05,952
God damn it!

824
01:31:08,753 --> 01:31:12,480
I think they're coming through.
That tunnel's not going to hold.

825
01:31:23,718 --> 01:31:26,616
These rocks are not going to
hold them away much longer.

826
01:31:26,785 --> 01:31:28,376
Can't you go any faster?

827
01:31:39,451 --> 01:31:42,508
Steiner? Steiner!

828
01:33:39,848 --> 01:33:41,871
Jesus... no!

829
01:34:33,147 --> 01:34:34,442
Hunter?

830
01:34:54,646 --> 01:34:56,236
Are you one of them?

831
01:34:56,480 --> 01:34:58,207
Get that pig-sticker out of my face.

832
01:34:58,513 --> 01:34:59,536
Are you?

833
01:35:00,179 --> 01:35:02,111
What do you think?
Give me that bomb!

834
01:35:05,545 --> 01:35:06,806
Give me the fucking bomb!

835
01:35:15,213 --> 01:35:16,872
Shit! Here come
those motherfuckers.

836
01:36:03,977 --> 01:36:05,375
Anytime!

837
01:36:17,077 --> 01:36:18,940
Put the detonator in the hole.

838
01:36:19,111 --> 01:36:21,202
- You've got to be shitting.
- Put it in the hole!

839
01:36:21,378 --> 01:36:23,241
- Which hole?
- Any hole!

840
01:36:26,910 --> 01:36:27,876
This one...

841
01:36:31,577 --> 01:36:33,600
Piece of shit... it doesn't fit!

842
01:36:37,210 --> 01:36:38,198
There?

843
01:36:58,110 --> 01:36:59,905
- It's not working.
- What?

844
01:37:03,943 --> 01:37:05,909
Give me the pages from the book!

845
01:37:07,076 --> 01:37:08,837
- What are you doing?
- I'm working on it.

846
01:37:14,476 --> 01:37:15,703
I lost my sword.

847
01:37:18,075 --> 01:37:19,234
Here.

848
01:37:44,608 --> 01:37:45,938
Samuel?

849
01:37:46,541 --> 01:37:47,700
Legion.

850
01:37:52,942 --> 01:37:56,135
Severian, no! That's not Samuel.

851
01:38:19,674 --> 01:38:20,935
Duval, no!

852
01:38:26,107 --> 01:38:27,368
Kill him.

853
01:38:32,640 --> 01:38:33,799
Kill him.

854
01:38:46,973 --> 01:38:49,405
You are Samuel. It's alright.

855
01:40:04,338 --> 01:40:05,360
That's for Nathan.

856
01:40:06,105 --> 01:40:07,468
That's for El Jesus.

857
01:40:10,637 --> 01:40:12,035
And this is for Samuel.

858
01:40:48,170 --> 01:40:49,294
Jump!

859
01:40:52,037 --> 01:40:53,195
Jump!

860
01:40:56,670 --> 01:40:58,226
Have Faith.

861
01:42:45,767 --> 01:42:47,494
<i>And so it ended... </i>

862
01:42:47,734 --> 01:42:50,461
<i>I failed, he did not. </i>

863
01:42:52,033 --> 01:42:53,999
<i>Apostate, unbeliever. </i>

864
01:42:55,700 --> 01:42:56,995
<i>Saviour. </i>

